frus:attachment.p:
Payments in kind can be made from the following sources:
a)
Stocks of goodsOther than those subject to restitution which would not be credited against reparation. [Footnote in the original.];
b)
Existing capital equipmentOther than those subject to restitution which would not be credited against reparation. [Footnote in the original.];
c)
Current production of goods and services;
d)
Direct labor services.
